But also, I created him.

491
00:15:47,601 --> 00:15:48,907
Hey.

492
00:15:54,216 --> 00:15:56,393
- McCallister, your lawyer
has more questions for you.

493
00:15:56,436 --> 00:15:57,524
- What?
- Why were you doing that?

494
00:15:57,568 --> 00:15:59,047
- You said I should listen!

495
00:15:59,091 --> 00:16:01,572
- Well, listening doesn't
always mean being quiet.

496
00:16:01,615 --> 00:16:03,269
Sometimes,
the only way to listen

497
00:16:03,313 --> 00:16:04,662
is to say something.

498
00:16:04,705 --> 00:16:06,577
I'm listening to you right now.

499
00:16:06,620 --> 00:16:09,101
Do you see how I listen?
This is me listening.

500
00:16:09,144 --> 00:16:10,581
- You're pissing me off, Boyle!

501
00:16:10,624 --> 00:16:12,713
- Ah, and he's back!
Hold on to that aggression.

502
00:16:12,757 --> 00:16:14,019
Yeah, go!
Go, go, go!

503
00:16:16,326 --> 00:16:18,110
- What are you looking at?

504
00:16:18,153 --> 00:16:20,025
- McCallister.

505
00:16:20,068 --> 00:16:21,766
Terry, Terry, Terry.

506
00:16:21,809 --> 00:16:23,594
I need you to help me see
what I'm not seeing.

507
00:16:23,637 --> 00:16:24,769
Why can't you do this?

508
00:16:24,812 --> 00:16:26,684
- You're giving me
too many notes.

509
00:16:26,727 --> 00:16:29,948
- Okay, well, then I can boil
it down for you into one note:

510
00:16:29,991 --> 00:16:31,384
Tyrone is an ocean.

511
00:16:31,428 --> 00:16:32,994
- I don't know what that means.

512
00:16:33,038 --> 00:16:34,779
- It means I want you
to be tough but vulnerable,

513
00:16:34,822 --> 00:16:36,955
brave but scared,
jittery but perfectly still.

514
00:16:36,998 --> 00:16:39,392
Also, pace it up a little.
Come on, buddy, you got this.

515
00:16:39,436 --> 00:16:41,351
- Man, these stupid cops
won't leave me alone.

516
00:16:41,394 --> 00:16:43,353
What the hell?
They think I'm a snitch?

517
00:16:43,396 --> 00:16:44,658
Not me.
- I hear that.

518
00:16:44,702 --> 00:16:46,138
- McCallister,
I need to talk to you.

519
00:16:46,181 --> 00:16:47,226
- No!
- Excuse me?

520
00:16:47,269 --> 00:16:48,445
- I don't want any more notes.

521
00:16:48,488 --> 00:16:49,881
I've gone undercover before.

522
00:16:49,924 --> 00:16:51,752
Now just back off
and let me do this!

523
00:16:53,928 --> 00:16:55,103
- Uh-oh, Alfonso,

524
00:16:55,147 --> 00:16:58,019
seems as though we got a pig
in our midst.

525
00:16:58,063 --> 00:16:59,673
Looks like we can only trust
each other.

526
00:16:59,717 --> 00:17:01,806
- Come on, man,
you're obviously a cop too.

527
00:17:01,849 --> 00:17:04,156
You keep talking
about how nefarious you are.

528
00:17:04,199 --> 00:17:05,679
- Jake, let us in!

529
00:17:05,723 --> 00:17:07,202
- I think she's gonna be okay,

530
00:17:07,246 --> 00:17:08,813
but she's probably got
a low-grade concussion.

531
00:17:08,856 --> 00:17:10,989
I wish you hadn't tried
to do a death drop.

532
00:17:11,032 --> 00:17:13,513
- The ladies on "Drag Race"
make it look so easy.

533
00:17:13,557 --> 00:17:15,036
I know, you don't get
that reference because

534
00:17:15,080 --> 00:17:16,951
you don't have a television.
- Why?

535
00:17:16,995 --> 00:17:19,258
- Amy, I'm sorry for getting
so competitive back there.

536
00:17:19,301 --> 00:17:21,216
You guys are helping me out,
and I should just be grateful.

537
00:17:21,260 --> 00:17:23,654
- Of course you're being nice
to me when I'm being a monster.

538
00:17:23,697 --> 00:17:25,351
Well, you know what,
Mr. Perfect?

539
00:17:25,395 --> 00:17:26,657
I'm gonna find that ledger,

540
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:28,006
and I'm gonna save
your stupid butt.

541
00:17:28,049 --> 00:17:30,487
- That would be so great.
- Please stop.

542
00:17:30,530 --> 00:17:31,531
- Maybe there's a hidden panel
somewhere?

543
00:17:31,575 --> 00:17:32,532
- It's not in the desk.

544
00:17:32,576 --> 00:17:33,968
I bet it's in this old safe.

545
00:17:34,012 --> 00:17:35,405
- That seems like
a lot of work to open

546
00:17:35,448 --> 00:17:36,797
every time
you have to pay a bribe.

547
00:17:36,841 --> 00:17:39,887
I would keep it
in this filing cabinet.

548
00:17:41,715 --> 00:17:43,674
I found it!

549
00:17:43,717 --> 00:17:45,589
I beat the golden boy!
I'm the golden girl!

550
00:17:45,632 --> 00:17:46,981
- Hey, open up!

551
00:17:47,025 --> 00:17:48,418
Who's in there?
- Okay, everybody out.

552
00:17:48,461 --> 00:17:49,984
Go! Go, go, go!

553
00:17:52,334 --> 00:17:53,684
Hey, get off me!

554
00:17:53,727 --> 00:17:55,990
My God, you're even more
stunning up close.

555
00:17:59,864 --> 00:18:01,474
- I called for backup,
but it could take ten minutes.

556
00:18:01,518 --> 00:18:02,780
- Should we storm the place?
- Too late.

557
00:18:02,823 --> 00:18:04,129
Look,
they're bringing Jake out.

558
00:18:04,172 --> 00:18:06,610
- I told you, I was in the
office because I work there,

559
00:18:06,653 --> 00:18:08,133
and we've actually met
a bunch of times,

560
00:18:08,176 --> 00:18:09,395
and it's crazy
you don't remember me!

561
00:18:09,439 --> 00:18:10,788
- What should we do?
If they get away,

562
00:18:10,831 --> 00:18:12,180
we'll never be able
to track them.

563
00:18:12,224 --> 00:18:13,834
- Shoot out the tires.

564
00:18:13,878 --> 00:18:15,009
- You're a way better shot
than me.

565
00:18:15,053 --> 00:18:16,533
You should do it.
- Are you crazy?

566
00:18:16,576 --> 00:18:18,230
You're the golden girl.
- David, take the shot.

567
00:18:18,273 --> 00:18:19,492
- I just don't want you to feel
bad about yourself—

568
00:18:19,536 --> 00:18:20,580
- Take the shot!

569
00:18:24,541 --> 00:18:27,326
- You're under arrest,
you beautiful man.

570
00:18:27,369 --> 00:18:29,676
Cuff this son of a bitch.

571
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:32,157
Oh, my God,
you also smell so good.

572
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:34,812
Brazil!

573
00:18:34,855 --> 00:18:36,509
- All right,
so first things first,

574
00:18:36,553 --> 00:18:38,163
I think I owe you both
something,

575
00:18:38,206 --> 00:18:41,122
and it's this.

576
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:42,907
- Stop clapping!
There's nothing to clap about.

577
00:18:42,950 --> 00:18:45,344
- Look, I know you're upset,
but everything went great.

578
00:18:45,387 --> 00:18:47,215
- Great?
You ruined this mission.

579
00:18:47,259 --> 00:18:48,695
- Yeah, we might have
gotten him to talk

580
00:18:48,739 --> 00:18:50,480
if you didn't give me notes
every two seconds.

581
00:18:50,523 --> 00:18:53,091
- Guys, you performed exactly
the way I expected you to.

582
00:18:53,134 --> 00:18:55,702
It's just that you were both
supporting characters.

583
00:18:55,746 --> 00:18:57,356
- Hey, Boyle,
I did what you asked.

584
00:18:57,399 --> 00:18:58,705
Alfonso told me everything.

585
00:18:58,749 --> 00:18:59,967
- Yes! I knew it would work.

586
00:19:00,011 --> 00:19:01,360
- What?
What's going on?

587
00:19:01,403 --> 00:19:03,101
- You were never my real star,
Sarge.

588
00:19:03,144 --> 00:19:04,624
But I needed to create a scene

589
00:19:04,668 --> 00:19:07,018
so that Alfonso would think
that my mission had failed.

590
00:19:07,061 --> 00:19:08,672
Then I could send in...

591
00:19:08,715 --> 00:19:11,892
- Ricki Sheetz, DJ by night,
gun smuggler by later night.

592
00:19:11,936 --> 00:19:13,372
Alfonso started telling me

593
00:19:13,415 --> 00:19:15,026
about all the crazy crap
you guys pulled in there.

594
00:19:15,069 --> 00:19:16,331
He just couldn't stop talking

595
00:19:16,375 --> 00:19:18,029
till he gave me the name
of his supplier.

596
00:19:18,072 --> 00:19:20,379
- Rosa was my leading lady
from the start.

597
00:19:20,422 --> 00:19:22,076
She's the only good actor here.
- She is?

598
00:19:22,120 --> 00:19:23,469
- Yeah, you know nothing
about my real life.

599
00:19:23,513 --> 00:19:25,906
I'm always acting.
- Well done, Boyle.

600
00:19:25,950 --> 00:19:28,561
You've executed this mission
flawlessly. I'm impressed.

601
00:19:28,605 --> 00:19:31,042
- Wait, if you were gonna use
Diaz the whole time,

602
00:19:31,085 --> 00:19:32,347
why didn't you just
tell us that?

603
00:19:32,391 --> 00:19:33,871
- Because you two
would have given it away

604
00:19:33,914 --> 00:19:35,133
with your terrible acting.

605
00:19:35,176 --> 00:19:36,482
No offense,
but I can read

606
00:19:36,526 --> 00:19:38,571
every emotion you're feeling
on your face.

607
00:19:38,615 --> 00:19:40,486
- Can you read this one?
- Actually, yes.

608
00:19:40,530 --> 00:19:42,706
You're trying to be tough,
but inside,

609
00:19:42,749 --> 00:19:46,579
you're super impressed by what
I've accomplished today.

610
00:19:46,623 --> 00:19:48,886
- Damn, you're right.
You're good.

611
00:19:48,929 --> 00:19:51,889
- Thank you, everyone,
for joining me again.

612
00:19:51,932 --> 00:19:53,543
To David.
You're my hero.

613
00:19:53,586 --> 00:19:55,632
- And to Amy.
You saved my butt.

614
00:19:55,675 --> 00:19:58,069
You're a great cop
and a great sister.

615
00:19:58,112 --> 00:20:01,638
- Wow. That means a lot
coming from you.

616
00:20:01,681 --> 00:20:03,248
You've always been a role model
for me.

617
00:20:03,291 --> 00:20:04,902
- He's everyone's role model.

618
00:20:04,945 --> 00:20:06,207
That's why he's on the mantel.

619
00:20:07,948 --> 00:20:10,168
I have to go to the bathroom.

620
00:20:12,257 --> 00:20:13,693
- Hey, are you okay?

621
00:20:13,737 --> 00:20:15,347
- Yeah, I just had to go
to the bathroom, like I said.

622
00:20:15,390 --> 00:20:16,740
- Oh, great.
I thought you went in there

623
00:20:16,783 --> 00:20:18,437
to give yourself a pep talk
in the mirror

624
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:19,699
like the girl
from the deodorant commercial.

625
00:20:19,743 --> 00:20:21,266
- I don't know
what you're referring to.

626
00:20:21,309 --> 00:20:22,397
- She wants the big promotion,

627
00:20:22,441 --> 00:20:23,747
but there's just one problem.

628
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:25,662
She got skunk pit.
We'll watch it later.

629
00:20:25,705 --> 00:20:27,315
The point is,
I came to comfort you.

630
00:20:27,359 --> 00:20:30,405
- Aw, thanks, but I actually
feel really great.

631
00:20:30,449 --> 00:20:33,278
I've spent my whole life trying
to beat David at something,

632
00:20:33,321 --> 00:20:36,107
but when you were in danger,

633
00:20:36,150 --> 00:20:38,283
I just didn't care anymore.

634
00:20:38,326 --> 00:20:40,764
All I wanted was for you
to be okay.

635
00:20:40,807 --> 00:20:43,636
I may never have the mantel,
but it doesn't matter,

636
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:44,898
'cause I have you.

637
00:20:44,942 --> 00:20:46,247
- Well, I'm very proud of you,

638
00:20:46,291 --> 00:20:47,466
and I also wish
you had told me that

639
00:20:47,509 --> 00:20:48,772
before you went
to the bathroom,

640
00:20:48,815 --> 00:20:50,512
because I really roasted
your mom back there.

641
00:20:50,556 --> 00:20:52,863
And another thing,
you should appreciate Amy more,

642
00:20:52,906 --> 00:20:54,255
because she's amazing.

643
00:20:54,299 --> 00:20:55,779
And another thing,
when you come to visit us,

644
00:20:55,822 --> 00:20:57,302
you don't have to bring
your own coffee.

645
00:20:57,345 --> 00:20:58,608
Our coffee is fine.

646
00:20:58,651 --> 00:21:00,435
And another thing,
I know enough Spanish

647
00:21:00,479 --> 00:21:01,959
to understand what
idiota means!

648
00:21:02,002 --> 00:21:03,308
And another thing!

649
00:21:03,351 --> 00:21:05,353
When you say I have
an "interesting nose,"

650
00:21:05,397 --> 00:21:07,442
I know you mean big!

651
00:21:07,486 --> 00:21:09,183
I got lost in it.

652
00:21:09,227 --> 00:21:11,185
There were, like,
35 "another things."

653
00:21:11,229 --> 00:21:12,970
I'm so sorry.
- It's okay.

654
00:21:13,013 --> 00:21:14,449
You were defending my honor.

655
00:21:14,493 --> 00:21:15,973
And I'm glad
you said something.

656
00:21:16,016 --> 00:21:18,323
- So should I go back
and apologize to your mom?

657
00:21:18,366 --> 00:21:19,585
- Oh, hell no.
We're sneaking out the back.

658
00:21:19,629 --> 00:21:21,326
- Oh, thank God.
She is terrifying.

659
00:21:21,369 --> 00:21:23,197
See ya at Thanksgiving,
Mrs. Santiago.

660
00:21:23,241 --> 00:21:25,199
- Not a doctor.
- Shh.

661
00:21:25,243 --> 00:21:27,506
- Fremulon.

